5 SECTION 4. The subsection of Arkansas Constitution, Article 5, § 1,
6 titled "Verification", is amended to read as follows:
7 Verification. Only legal votes shall be counted upon petitions.
8 Petitions may be circulated and presented in parts, but each part of any
9 petition shall have attached thereto the affidavit of the person circulating
10 the same, that all signatures thereon were made in the presence of the
11 affiant, and that to the best of the affiant's knowledge and belief each
12 signature is genuine, and that the person signing is a legal voter and no
13 other affidavit or verification shall be required to establish the
14 genuineness of such signatures.
